üß© OpenShift Prerequisites and System Requirements

‚öôÔ∏è 1Ô∏è‚É£ Supported Operating Systems
OpenShift runs on RHEL CoreOS (RHCOS) or Red Hat Enterprise Linux (RHEL) depending on your setup:
| Component              | Recommended OS                                                 |
| ---------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Control Plane (Master) | **RHEL CoreOS** (default, auto-provisioned by installer)       |
| Worker Nodes           | **RHEL CoreOS** or **RHEL 8/9** (manual registration possible) |
| Bootstrap Node         | **RHEL CoreOS** (temporary during installation)                |
üß† RHCOS is a minimal, immutable OS optimized for OpenShift ‚Äî managed by MachineConfig Operator (MCO).

üñ•Ô∏è 2Ô∏è‚É£ Minimum Hardware Requirements
üß± A. Standard Cluster (3 Control + 2+ Worker Nodes)
| Node Type                  | vCPU | RAM    | Disk   | Notes                                  |
| -------------------------- | ---- | ------ | ------ | -------------------------------------- |
| **Bootstrap**              | 4    | 16 GB  | 120 GB | Temporary; removed after install       |
| **Master (Control Plane)** | 4+   | 16+ GB | 120 GB | Runs etcd, API, controllers, scheduler |
| **Worker Node**            | 2+   | 8+ GB  | 120 GB | Runs user workloads (Pods)             |
| **Infra Node (optional)**  | 4+   | 16+ GB | 120 GB | Hosts ingress, registry, monitoring    |
‚úÖ For production: 3 masters, minimum 2 workers (recommended 3+)

üß© B. Compact Cluster (3 nodes total)
Each node runs control plane + worker components.
| Node               | vCPU | RAM   | Disk    |
| ------------------ | ---- | ----- | ------- |
| Master+Worker (x3) | 8+   | 32 GB | 120 GB+ |
üîπ Minimum 3 nodes for HA (etcd quorum)

üß© C. Single Node OpenShift (SNO)
| Node        | vCPU | RAM   | Disk   |
| ----------- | ---- | ----- | ------ |
| Single node | 8    | 32 GB | 120 GB |
üîπ No HA, suitable for edge or PoC.

üåê 3Ô∏è‚É£ Networking Requirements
üî∏ A. Network Topology
OpenShift assumes a flat Layer 3 network with full connectivity between:
Bootstrap ‚Üî Master ‚Üî Worker nodes
API Load Balancer and all nodes
DNS resolution (forward and reverse)

üî∏ B. Ports and Protocols
| Purpose                       | Port(s)   | Protocol | Source ‚Üí Destination     |
| ----------------------------- | --------- | -------- | ------------------------ |
| **API Server**                | 6443      | TCP      | Clients ‚Üí Masters        |
| **etcd**                      | 2379‚Äì2380 | TCP      | Masters ‚Üî Masters        |
| **Machine Config / Ignition** | 22623     | TCP      | Bootstrap ‚Üí Nodes        |
| **Ingress / Apps**            | 80, 443   | TCP      | External ‚Üí Workers/Infra |
| **SSH (optional)**            | 22        | TCP      | Admin ‚Üí All nodes        |

üî∏ C. DNS Records (Required)
| Record Type       | Example                   | Description                    |
| ----------------- | ------------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| **API endpoint**  | `api.ocp.example.com`     | Used by CLI and web console    |
| **Internal API**  | `api-int.ocp.example.com` | Internal cluster communication |
| **Wildcard apps** | `*.apps.ocp.example.com`  | Routes for all OpenShift apps  |
All must resolve to your Load Balancer VIP or appropriate node IPs.

üî∏ D. Load Balancer Requirements
You must configure load balancers for:
API Server: TCP 6443 (masters)
Ingress Controller: TCP 80, 443 (workers/infra)
Machine Config Server: TCP 22623 (bootstrap/master)
For UPI, you configure these manually.
For IPI, installer creates them automatically (e.g., AWS ELB).

üîë 4Ô∏è‚É£ Authentication & Access Requirements
| Requirement              | Details                                                          |
| ------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **SSH Key**              | Needed to access CoreOS nodes for debugging (`core` user)        |
| **Pull Secret**          | Required from Red Hat Customer Portal to access container images |
| **Base Domain**          | Example: `example.com` (must be managed by DNS)                  |
| **Cluster Name**         | Example: `ocp`, resulting in `ocp.example.com`                   |
| **Red Hat Subscription** | Needed for RHEL systems & support entitlements                   |

‚òÅÔ∏è 5Ô∏è‚É£ Cloud / Virtualization Prerequisites
üî∏ For IPI (Cloud)
| Platform    | Requirements                                            |
| ----------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| **AWS**     | IAM access, Route53 zone, EC2, VPC, ELB permissions     |
| **Azure**   | Subscription, Service Principal credentials             |
| **GCP**     | Service account with compute & DNS permissions          |
| **vSphere** | Datacenter, cluster, datastore, VM template permissions |

üî∏ For UPI (On-prem or KVM)
| Component         | Requirement                      |
| ----------------- | -------------------------------- |
| **Hypervisor**    | KVM, VMware, oVirt, etc.         |
| **Load Balancer** | HAProxy, F5, or Keepalived setup |
| **DNS Server**    | BIND, dnsmasq, or external DNS   |
| **Storage**       | NFS, iSCSI, Ceph, or local PVs   |

üßÆ 7Ô∏è‚É£ Resource Summary Table
| Component | vCPU | Memory | Disk   | Count    | Purpose                       |
| --------- | ---- | ------ | ------ | -------- | ----------------------------- |
| Bootstrap | 4    | 16 GB  | 120 GB | 1        | Temporary install helper      |
| Master    | 4    | 16 GB  | 120 GB | 3        | Control Plane                 |
| Worker    | 2    | 8 GB   | 120 GB | 2+       | Workload nodes                |
| Infra     | 4    | 16 GB  | 120 GB | Optional | Ingress, registry, monitoring |

üß† 9Ô∏è‚É£ Preflight Checklist

‚úÖ RHCOS/RHEL base images downloaded
‚úÖ Pull secret ready
‚úÖ SSH key generated and added
‚úÖ DNS records created
‚úÖ Load balancers configured
‚úÖ Sufficient CPU/RAM/disk
‚úÖ Internet or local mirror (for air-gapped)
‚úÖ Network ports open between nodes
‚úÖ Subscription or entitlement configured

üìä Summary
| Category    | Requirement                                        |
| ----------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| OS          | RHEL CoreOS / RHEL 8/9                             |
| CPU         | 4‚Äì8 vCPUs (min), 8+ recommended for production     |
| Memory      | 16 GB min per master, 8+ per worker                |
| Storage     | 120 GB min per node                                |
| Network     | Static IPs, DNS, LBs, open ports                   |
| Tools       | `openshift-install`, `oc`, `kubectl`               |
| Credentials | SSH key, Pull secret, Domain, Red Hat subscription |

